definitions.definition: A writ issued out of the Chancery for the payment of a pension , debt , the delivery of one's land or goods from a sheriff 's custody, the delivery a prisoner put in bail fo appearance or other royal allowance .

main_definition: ( obsolete , historical , law ) A writ issued out of the Chancery for the payment of a pension , debt , the delivery of one's land or goods from a sheriff 's custody, the delivery a prisoner put in bail fo appearance or other royal allowance .
